<br>
&quot;What gates?&quot; he asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;The front gates with the guards.  You know, facing Nro?&quot; I replied assuming that by 52, you'd know wtf the front gate is.<br>
<br>
He's quiet for a few minutes then sends me another tell saying he's in some &quot;market pit.&quot; WTF? I thought so I gave him a /loc.  Then I said, &quot;you're a ranger, track me.&quot;<br>
<br>
It literally took him over 30 minutes to find me in a small zone like EFP.  How much more ebay can one person scream?  LOL I just about laughed the whole time.  Call me evil, but I wasn't about to try to find him.  I wanted the &quot;thrill of the kill&quot; so to speak and make him work for his xloc.  Anyone post 20 can find their way around FP in this stage of EQ. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><CENTER>
